obo:UBERON_0002037  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4553  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 5a: CACNG7 KD granule cells show a decrease in synaptic channel conductance (to 8.9 ± 0.6 pS, n = 9, P = 0.0093) as compared to WT.\n\nFigure 4: CACNG7 KD does not affect synaptic localisation of AMPA receptors.\n\nAlthough γ-7 is not essential for synaptic localization of AMPA receptors, the reduction in single-channel conductance suggests that after knockdown of γ-7, the postsynaptic AMPARs may be either TARPless or composed of subunits (such as homomeric GluA2) that give rise to low-conductance channels.. Experimental description: \"ONLINE METHODS\nMice. Individual male and female C57BL/6 (WT) and stargazer (stg/stg) mice (postnatal day (P) 4-7) were used to prepare dissociated cultures of cerebellar granule cells.\"\n\n\"After γ-7 knockdown in WT granule cells, we still detected mEPSCs (Fig. 5a), ... \"\n\n\"These results are in accord with observations from knockout mice showing that the relative expression of TARPs γ-2 and γ-7 influences AMPAR subunit composition\"\n\n\"For knockdown of TARP γ-7, cells were transfected with a mixture of four shRNA expression constructs against γ-7 (GeneCopoeia, MSH037278-mU6; 2 μg per coverslip). The target sequences used were mouse γ-7 (accession code NM_133189.3), 54 (5'-CTGCGGCCTGCTCCTTGTG-3'), 176 (5'-GGAGAGTCTGCTTCTTTGC-3'), 374 (5'-CTCAGAGGACCATTCTTGC-3') and 500 (5'-CTGAGCAGTACTTTCACTA-3')\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-04-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4553" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

